<subSubSection id="C31B657ACC2AFFDDFEFE81CF9FE0FD18" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2AFFDDFEFE81CF9E3BF8F5" blockId="33.[204,699,1749,1803]" box="[362,541,1782,1803]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">
<heading id="D0F6819DCC2AFFDDFEFE81CF9E3BF8F5" box="[362,541,1782,1803]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFEFE81CF9E3BF8F5" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[362,541,1782,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFEFE81CF9E3BF8F5" box="[362,541,1782,1803]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">DOLICHOCOLON</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2AFFDDFF0480259FE0FD18" blockId="33.[144,759,1820,1903]" lastBlockId="33.[806,1422,198,1657]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">
Recently 
<bibRefCitation id="EF904B00CC2AFFDDFE9480259D94F8CE" author="Cerretti P" box="[256,434,1820,1842]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" pagination="51 - 63" refId="ref21854" refString="Cerretti P. 2009. A review of the genus Kuwanimyia Townsend (Diptera: Tachinidae), with taxonomic remarks on related genera. African Entomology 17: 51 - 63." type="journal article" year="2009">Cerretti (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, discussing the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFF5480039D77F8B3" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[192,337,1850,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFF5480039D77F8B3" box="[192,337,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFEF880029DD8F8AC" authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1916" box="[364,510,1851,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Kuwanimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFEF880029DD8F8AC" box="[364,510,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Kuwanimyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, failed to assess relationships between these two genera and 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFD0D80609833FF20" authority="Villeneuve. Careful" authorityName="Villeneuve. Careful" authorityYear="1929" box="[665,1045,198,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Palesisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFD0D80609ED1F892" box="[665,759,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Palesisa</emphasis>
Villeneuve. Careful
</taxonomicName>
examination of all species ascribed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFC3D87DD9821FF05" authorityName="Villeneuve. Careful" authorityYear="1929" box="[937,1031,228,249]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Palesisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFC3D87DD9821FF05" box="[937,1031,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Palesisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by one of us (P. C.) suggested that it could be considered a good candidate as sistergroup of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFC0F861B980AFECB" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[923,1068,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFC0F861B980AFECB" box="[923,1068,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFBD3861B98FFFECB" authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1916" box="[1095,1241,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Kuwanimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFBD3861B98FFFECB" box="[1095,1241,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Kuwanimyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Indeed, 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFAC7861B9F74FEAA" authorityName="Villeneuve. Careful" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Palesisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFAC7861B9F74FEAA" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Palesisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows the same combination of character states used by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF904B00CC2AFFDDFC028666986EFE89" author="Cerretti P" box="[918,1096,351,373]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" pagination="51 - 63" refId="ref21854" refString="Cerretti P. 2009. A review of the genus Kuwanimyia Townsend (Diptera: Tachinidae), with taxonomic remarks on related genera. African Entomology 17: 51 - 63." type="journal article" year="2009">Cerretti (2009)</bibRefCitation>
to support a sister-group relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFBB786449892FE6E" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[1059,1204,381,402]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFBB786449892FE6E" box="[1059,1204,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFB60864799A0FE6F" authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1916" box="[1268,1414,382,403]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Kuwanimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFB60864799A0FE6F" box="[1268,1414,382,403]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Kuwanimyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely: (1) ocellar setae well developed and proclinate; (2) facial ridge with a row of setae over most of its length; (3) parafacial entirely bare; (4) lateral scutellar setae not differentiated; (5) hypandrium without a bridge-like sclerite between the hypandrial arms; (6) epiphallus not differentiated; and (7) dorsal process of distiphallus well developed and sclerotized. None of these features is unique within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFAAC854B99ABFD74" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[1336,1421,626,648]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Goniini">Goniini</taxonomicName>
but their combination unequivocally identifies this group of genera, which could be considered monophyletic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B657ACC2AFFD8FCAB85D49FA4FA79" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2AFFDDFCAB85D49902FCC3" blockId="33.[806,1422,198,1657]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">
In this analysis, no apomorphies that support 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFAC785D49F74FCDD" authorityName="Villeneuve. Careful" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Palesisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFAC785D49F74FCDD" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Palesisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reveal that it could be considered paraphyletic with respect to 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFC4B84139857FCC3" authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1916" box="[991,1137,810,831]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Kuwanimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFC4B84139857FCC3" box="[991,1137,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Kuwanimyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFB188413993BFCC3" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[1164,1309,810,831]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFB188413993BFCC3" box="[1164,1309,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2AFFDDFCAB84709839FBAF" blockId="33.[806,1422,198,1657]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">
A sister-group relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFB68847199ABFCA1" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[1276,1421,840,861]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFB68847199ABFCA1" box="[1276,1421,840,861]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFCF584519FD5FC81" authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1916" box="[865,1011,872,893]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Kuwanimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFCF584519FD5FC81" box="[865,1011,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Kuwanimyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is corroborated by the following four autapomorphic character states: second aristomere at least three times as long as wide [1: 1], facial ridge with a row of stout erect setae over most of its length [4: 1; 5: 1], and notopleuron with an additional seta [7: 1]; these states may be observed in other unrelated 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFBED832698E8FBC9" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[1145,1230,1055,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Goniini">Goniini</taxonomicName>
not included in the present analysis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2AFFDDFCAB83659F5DFB17" blockId="33.[806,1422,198,1657]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">
Monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFC7483659854FB8D" authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1916" box="[992,1138,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Kuwanimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFC7483659854FB8D" box="[992,1138,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Kuwanimyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here supported by the following autapomorphic character states: four katepisternal setae [8: 1], apical scutellar setae strongly erect [9: 1], and not crossed at mid point [10: 1].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2AFFDDFCAB83CC9F98F985" blockId="33.[806,1422,198,1657]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">
At the present state of knowledge, monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFCB2822A9F91FAD4" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[806,951,1299,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFCB2822A9F91FAD4" box="[806,951,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is corroborated by the following autapomorphies: one strong and isolated upper reclinate orbital seta [3: 1] (
<figureCitation id="133A2A74CC2AFFDDFB958268987AFA9A" box="[1025,1116,1361,1383]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[164,243,1058,1077]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,1027]" captionTargetId="figure-359@4.[323,1283,196,1027]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Dolichocolon chiangmaiensis sp. nov. (holotype). A, head in lateral view; B, abdomen in dorsal view; C, terminalia in lateral view (arrow indicates hypandrial arm); D, distal 1/2 of cerci and surstylus in lateral view; E, terminalia in posterior view; F, pregonite, postgonite, and phallus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440705" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440705/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Figs 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A2A74CC2AFFDDFBFC826898ACFA9A" box="[1128,1162,1361,1382]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[144,223,1390,1409]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1361]" captionTargetId="figure-186@5.[303,1263,195,1361]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Dolichocolon angoramensis sp. nov. (holotype). A, head in lateral view; B, presutural portion of mesonotum in dorsal view; C, abdomen in dorsal view; D, terminalia in lateral view; E, cerci and surstyli in anterolateral view; F, terminalia in posterior view; G, distal 1/3 of cerci and surstyli in posterior view (arrow indicates the brush of flattened setae)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440707" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440707/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A2A74CC2AFFDDFB028268989EFA9A" box="[1174,1208,1361,1382]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="15.[144,223,1097,1116]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,196,1068]" captionTargetId="figure-290@15.[303,1263,196,1068]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 9. Dolichocolon rude sp. nov. (holotype). A, head in lateral view; B, presutural portion of scutum in dorsolateral view; C, abdomen in dorsal view; D, terminalia in lateral view; E, cerci and surstylus in lateral view; F, terminalia in posterior view; G, apical portion of cerci in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440721/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">9A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133A2A74CC2AFFDDFB51826898D3FA9B" box="[1221,1269,1361,1383]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="20.[164,243,1215,1234]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,197,1185]" captionTargetId="figure-228@20.[323,1283,197,1185]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 13. Dolichocolon orientale Townsend. A, head in lateral view (Berastagi, Sumatra); B, abdomen in dorsal view (Berastagi, Sumatra); C, same (Yunnan, China); D, same (Honshu, Japan); E–G, holotype of D. orientale: E, terminalia in lateral view; F, terminalia in posterior view; G, right half of cerci and surstylus in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440729/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">13A</figureCitation>
), which is an unquestionable homoplasy because several other unrelated goniine and eryciine genera share this state, and wing cells dm and sc with a conspicuous bare dorsal surface (
<figureCitation id="133A2A74CC2AFFDDFBBC82F2985DFA1D" box="[1064,1147,1483,1505]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="9.[144,223,1103,1122]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1073]" captionTargetId="figure-268@9.[303,1263,195,1073]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 6. Dolichocolon paradoxum Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm. A, anterobasal portion of right wing in dorsal view (Rome, Italy) (bare surface of cells dm (discal-medial) and sc (subcostal) in red); B, epandrial complex in lateral view (Bosco della Ficuzza, Sicily, Italy); C, epandrial complex in posterior view (Maputo Special Reserve, Mozambique); D, distal portion of cerci and medial surface of left surstylus in posterolateral view (Bosco della Ficuzza, Sicily, Italy)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440715/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
) [11: 1]. Interestingly, this latter character state is shared by all 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFA8382D39F6CF9E1" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFA8382D39F6CF9E1" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens examined and was not found in any other goniines of which we are aware, providing strong autapomorphic support for the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFCB2815D9F91F985" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[806,951,1636,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFCB2815D9F91F985" box="[806,951,1636,1657]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2AFFDDFCC681819944F931" blockId="33.[850,1378,1720,1741]" box="[850,1378,1720,1741]" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">PHYLOGENY AND SPECIES- GROUP DEFINITIONS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2AFFD8FCB281E79DC2FC46" blockId="33.[806,1421,1758,1903]" lastBlockId="36.[164,779,902,1903]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2AFFDDFCB281E79852F90F" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[806,1140,1758,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiangmaiensis">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2AFFDDFCB281E79852F90F" box="[806,1140,1758,1779]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Dolichocolon chiangmaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
takes up a position as sister group to ‘Group A’ both under equal weights (
<figureCitation id="133A2A74CC2AFFDDFCBA80259FA7F8CE" box="[814,897,1820,1842]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[144,223,1648,1667]" captionTargetBox="[146,1422,193,1614]" captionTargetId="figure-0@3.[144,1424,193,1618]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogeny of Dolichocolon. A, strict consensus of two equally parsimonious trees resulting from an analysis with equal weights and all characters treated as unordered, numbers on branches denote Bremer support values; B, jackknife resampling percentiles with cut-off of 50%; C, tree obtained under implied weights (default function) and concavity factor k ± 12; D, tree obtained under implied weights (default function) and concavity factor 1 ³ k ³ 11." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440703/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) and implied weights (
<figureCitation id="133A2A74CC2AFFDDFB068025992DF8CD" box="[1170,1291,1820,1842]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[144,223,1648,1667]" captionTargetBox="[146,1422,193,1614]" captionTargetId="figure-0@3.[144,1424,193,1618]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogeny of Dolichocolon. A, strict consensus of two equally parsimonious trees resulting from an analysis with equal weights and all characters treated as unordered, numbers on branches denote Bremer support values; B, jackknife resampling percentiles with cut-off of 50%; C, tree obtained under implied weights (default function) and concavity factor k ± 12; D, tree obtained under implied weights (default function) and concavity factor 1 ³ k ³ 11." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440703/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Fig. 1C, D</figureCitation>
); this node also received good resampling support (
<figureCitation id="133A2A74CC2AFFDDFB6680039960F8AC" box="[1266,1350,1850,1872]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[144,223,1648,1667]" captionTargetBox="[146,1422,193,1614]" captionTargetId="figure-0@3.[144,1424,193,1618]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogeny of Dolichocolon. A, strict consensus of two equally parsimonious trees resulting from an analysis with equal weights and all characters treated as unordered, numbers on branches denote Bremer support values; B, jackknife resampling percentiles with cut-off of 50%; C, tree obtained under implied weights (default function) and concavity factor k ± 12; D, tree obtained under implied weights (default function) and concavity factor 1 ³ k ³ 11." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5440703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5440703/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="577">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). It is interesting to point out the number of plesiomorphies found in the male terminalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FDA784BF9F2DFC67" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[563,779,902,923]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiangmaiensis">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FDA784BF9F2DFC67" box="[563,779,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. chiangmaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(characters 13, 14, and 15).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2FFFD8FF2884FA9F27FBAE" blockId="36.[164,779,902,1903]" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">‘Group A’ forms a relatively well-supported monophyletic assemblage characterized by having a wide posterior margin of lateral lobe of sternite 5 [13: 1], some long robust setae on sternite 5 [14: 1], and by having hypandrial arms not bent anteriorly [15: 1].</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2FFFD8FF2883659D12F8EF" blockId="36.[164,779,902,1903]" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FF6483659DA8FB8D" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[240,398,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angoramensis">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FF6483659DA8FB8D" box="[240,398,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">angoramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group is characterized by having setae on medial extension of surstylus [23: 1], interpreted as secondarily lost in 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FDA483A39EF2FB52" authorityName="Mesnil. A" authorityYear="1968" box="[560,724,1177,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africanum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FDA483A39EF2FB52" box="[560,724,1177,1199]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. africanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FD6583A39D00FB31" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basilewskyi">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FD6583A39D00FB31" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. basilewskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FEAD83819DF5FB31" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[313,467,1208,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FEAD83819DF5FB31" box="[313,467,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. caudatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FE7283819E79FB31" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[486,607,1208,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesnili">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FE7283819E79FB31" box="[486,607,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. mesnili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FD3E83819F22FB31" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[682,772,1208,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rude">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FD3E83819F22FB31" box="[682,772,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. rude</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FF4383EE9D53FB10" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[215,373,1239,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angoramensis">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FF4383EE9D53FB10" box="[215,373,1239,1260]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">angoramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, and the position of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FD3E83EE9D2DFAF6" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angoramensis">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FD3E83EE9D2DFAF6" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. angoramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FE4D83CC9E69FAF6" authorityName="Mesnil. A" authorityYear="1968" box="[473,591,1269,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africanum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FE4D83CC9E69FAF6" box="[473,591,1269,1290]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">africanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, received no resampling support. The 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FD9D822A9E59FAD4" authorityName="Mesnil. A" authorityYear="1968" box="[521,639,1299,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africanum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FD9D822A9E59FAD4" box="[521,639,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">africanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group is a well-corroborated assemblage of species that share the following apomorphies: long and robust median marginal setae on abdominal tergite 3 [12: 1], shovel- or paddle-like, laterally flattened surstylus [17: 1], distal 1/3 of surstylus strongly bent posteriorly [18: 1], and well-developed and pointed medial preapical tooth of cerci [35: 2]. The last three character states also appear, rarely and very scattered, in some other goniine genera, such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FDD7811E9F21F9C1" authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1838" box="[579,775,1575,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Frontina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FDD7811E9E8EF9C0" box="[579,680,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">Frontina</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FF30817C9DBAF9A7" authority="Rondani" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[164,412,1605,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharipa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FF30817C9D02F9A6" box="[164,292,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">Blepharipa</emphasis>
Rondani
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FE6E817C9F20F9A7" authority="Macquart" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1851" box="[506,774,1605,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FE6E817C9E59F9A6" box="[506,639,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">Blepharella</emphasis>
Macquart
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the first one appears more commonly in several other unrelated genera. With the sole exception of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FF63819B9DBAF94A" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm. A" authorityYear="1889" box="[247,412,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paradoxum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FF63819B9DBAF94A" box="[247,412,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. paradoxum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is widespread in Africa, Mediterranean Europe, and the Middle East, all other species composing the 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FE2D81E79E09F90F" authorityName="Mesnil. A" authorityYear="1968" box="[441,559,1758,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africanum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FE2D81E79E09F90F" box="[441,559,1758,1779]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">africanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group are strictly Afrotropical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE36F1CC2FFFD8FF2880259FA4FA79" blockId="36.[164,779,902,1903]" lastBlockId="36.[826,1441,902,1413]" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">
The phylogenetic positions of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FD8C80259EB9F8CD" box="[536,671,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientale">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FD8C80259EB9F8CD" box="[536,671,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. orientale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister group of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FE8B80029D97F8B3" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[287,433,1850,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crosskeyi">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FE8B80029D97F8B3" box="[287,433,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. crosskeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FE5880029E0EF8AC" authorityName="Mesnil. A" authorityYear="1968" box="[460,552,1851,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FE5880029E0EF8AC" box="[460,552,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">vicinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, and of 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FD6580029D2FF892" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crosskeyi">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FD6580029D2FF892" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. crosskeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FE7280609E64F892" authorityName="Mesnil. A" authorityYear="1968" box="[486,578,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FE7280609E64F892" box="[486,578,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">vicinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, are indi- cated, respectively, by the evenly curved distal 1/2 of cerci [29: 1] and by the scarcely developed and rounded medial preapical tooth of cerci [35: 1]; both do not receive any resampling support. By contrast, monophyly of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FB8383389855FBEA" authorityName="Mesnil. A" authorityYear="1968" box="[1047,1139,1025,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FB8383389855FBEA" box="[1047,1139,1025,1046]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">vicinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group is corroborated by two synapomorphies: stout and massive distal 2/3 of surstylus [17: 2] and presence of a wrinkled membrane between medial margin of surstylus and posterolateral margin of cerci [25: 1]. This group, although it consists almost entirely of Oriental and Australasian elements, reaches the Afrotropical region with 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FC4483EE98AEFB10" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[976,1160,1239,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paravicinum">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FC4483EE98AEFB10" box="[976,1160,1239,1260]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. paravicinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for which a relatively well-supported sister-group relationship with the Oriental 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D72CC2FFFD8FC3F822D9825FAD4" authorityName="Cerretti &amp; Shima" authorityYear="2011" box="[939,1027,1299,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dolichocolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dali">
<emphasis id="B975EAE3CC2FFFD8FC3F822D9825FAD4" box="[939,1027,1299,1321]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">D. dali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found. This species is known from 
<collectingCountry id="F3167661CC2FFFD8FC4B820B980DFABB" box="[991,1067,1330,1351]" name="Yemen" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">Yemen</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3167661CC2FFFD8FBEF820B98F7FAB4" box="[1147,1233,1330,1352]" name="Nigeria" pageId="36" pageNumber="580">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
and is possibly widespread through the Arabian Peninsula and Sahel.
</paragraph>
